msItem.title: Ordo and Canon missae
Blessings of water and salt
msItem.incipit: Deus qui ad salutem humani generis maxima queque sacramenta in aquarum substantia condidisti
msItem.explicit: presta nobis quesumus domine per huius creature aspersionem sanitatem mentis integritatem corporis tutelam salutis securitatem spei corroborationem fidei hic et in eterna secula seculorum amen
msItem.note: The two blessings of water and salt have been added after the prefaces by a different medieval hand. A third blessing, in the same hand, is found on .

note.p:
Folio 14 is a singlteton which has been inserted into the quire; the recto exhibits a drawing in the Bohemian Beautiful Style in black ink and red, ocher and brown washes: the Virgin Mary seated with the Christ child on her lap; standing behind them, a young duke Wenceslaus, armed with sword and shield, girded and dressed in a cloak and mail. All three figures haloed. The drawing is dated by Kletzl to the 1370s ( Kletzl
).

The verso of the folio contains the final part of the blessing of the wine for the feast of St John the Apostle (Benedictio amoris sancti Iohannis); it begins at potencia ac benediccione qua in vltima temporali cena and ends with Bibite et inebriamini dilecti dei ebrietate salutis et prosperitatis corporum et animarum vestrarum et pociamur victoria sempiterna In nomine patris et filii et spriritus sancti amen
.

msItem.title: Exorcisms of salt and water
msItem.incipit: Exorans te creaturam salis in nomine dei
msItem.explicit: Fiat hec commixtio salis et aque pariter in nomine sancte et indiuidue trinitatis salutifera afficiatur in nomine patris et filii et spiritus sancti amen
msItem.note: The blessing of water and salt has been added after the instruction for the Communicantes prayers by a different medieval hand.

msItem.incipit: Dum offeretur hostia et calix dic

note.p: The Ordo begins with an instruction for the celebration of Holy Communion followed by prefaces ().
The Proper of time begins with advent Sunday and ends with a mass for the Virgin Mary and one for the angels.
The folium after has been torn out resulting in loss of text.

msItem.note: The section lists the proper mass prayers for certain specific occasions - , pro pace; , pro peccatis; , pro tribulatione; , pro humilitate; , communis oratio - with the rubric pro peccatis heading a complete mass description.

note.p: The readings for the different masses are collected into one section extending from to .
The proper of saints begins with the feast of St Andrew (30 November) and ends with the commemoration of St Linus (26 November).
